The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Anita Das, the yoga teacher whose slap had allegedly killed eight-year-old Iftesham on Friday, was sacked by the authorities of Vidya Bharati School in Mominpur on Monday as she did not surrender before police.     Washington resident Sampa Srivastava, 61, who was arrested in the city airport on Sunday for carrying five bullets in her luggage, was granted bail on Monday.    The Trinamul Congress MLA from Satgachhi, Sonali Guha, and her supporters accused of confining officers of Nodakhali police station on November 25, surrendered at Alipore court on Monday. They were granted bail.     Eight neurologists from the UK and the US will attend a three-day seminar on clinical neurology at Ramakrishna Mission Seva Pratishthan on December 4.     Sirajul Islam and nine others were awarded life sentence for murdering jeweller Yudhistir Majumder, a resident of Baduria, and looting his house 18 years ago.                                                                                                                                                              
